It&#8217;s understood four gunmen entered the Centurion restaurant on Tuesday but security guards chased them, leading to a shootout. JOHANNESBURG - A man has been killed and another critically injured after they allegedly tried to rob a restaurant in Clubview in Centurion.It s understood four gunmen entered the restaurant earlier on Tuesday but the owner called local security guards, who then chased the suspects, leading to a shootout and the death of one suspect.Two of the suspects have been arrested while the injured one is under police guard in hospital.